title: MSU meets Louisiana Tech at 11 a.m.
text:
MSU meets Louisiana Tech at 11 a.m. Michael Bonner, The Clarion-Ledger 12:56 p.m. CDT October 5, 2015 Mississippi State Bulldogs head coach Dan Mullen with his players before they enter M.M. Roberts Stadium to play the Southern Miss Golden Eagles. Mandatory Credit: Chuck Cook-USA TODAY Sports (Photo: Chuck Cook, Chuck Cook-USA TODAY Sports) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
STARKVILLE -- Mississippi State will have its first Saturday morning kick on Oct. 17. 
The Southeastern Conference announced the game times for Saturday, Oct. 17 on Monday. Mississippi State and Louisiana Tech will kickoff at 11 a.m. at Davis Wade Stadium on SEC Network. 
MSU has played four games that started later than 6 p.m. this year. It's only day came was kicked at 3 p.m. against Northwestern State. Mississippi State plays Troy this weekend at 3 p.m. 
The entire Oct. 17 television schedule within the SEC is as follows: 
Louisiana Tech at Mississippi State, 11 a.m. SEC Network 
Ole Miss at Memphis, 11 a.m. ABC 
Alabama at Texas A&M, 2:30 p.m. CBS 
Vanderbilt at South Carolina, 3 p.m SEC Network 
Florida at LSU, 6 p.m. ESPN 
Missouri at Georgia, 6:30 p.m. SEC Network
